translated:
Jannert, Tage Arvid Emanuel was a contract vicar and parish priest in Böda. He was born on March 26, 1904 in Ljungby and married Signe Jeansson in 1929. They had four children: Birgitta (born in 1931), Bertil (born in 1934), Bo Örjan (born in 1939), and Östen (born in 1944). 

Jannert completed his secondary studies in Kalmar in 1924 and his theological studies at Lund University in 1925. He passed his theological licensure and practical theology exam in 1928, and was ordained as a priest in the Växjö diocese in 1929. He served as an assistant pastor in Villstad and substitute pastor in Båraryd before becoming a curate in Ramkvilla. He served as the parish priest in Böda from 1936 and as contract vicar in the Ölands northern contract from 1946. He was a representative for the seamen's board and the diocesan council, chairman of the church council, school board, and Böda Red Cross district.

Jansén, Kurt Gustaf was a high school teacher in Motala. He was born on December 8, 1901 in Vårdnäs, Östergötland county. His parents were the cantor and elementary school teacher Johan Viktor Jansén and Anna Lindahl. He married Gunvor Castelli in 1931 and they had one child, Gun (born in 1934).

Jansén completed his secondary studies in Linköping in 1921 and his bachelor's degree in Uppsala in 1926. He completed his master's degree in 1928 and a probationary year in 1931. He traveled to England and France with a government scholarship in 1947. He was a language teacher at Katrineholm's comprehensive high school from 1928 to 1930, and a substitute teacher at Växjö's comprehensive high school. He was a primary school teacher in Växjö from 1931 to 1934. He was a substitute teacher at Stockholm's northern Latin high school from 1934 to 1937, an associate teacher there from 1938 to 1941, and a language teacher at Motala high school from 1941. He was also a substitute teacher at Motala's vocational school from 1940 to 1944.
